<TITLE> Plant at least three saplings: PM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 1 (bdnews24.com)--Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has called on all to plant at least three saplings on open spaces including campuses of educational institutions to protect environment. She made the appeal at the inauguration of a three-month National Tree Plantation Movement and one-month Tree Fair at Bangabandhu International Conference Centre on Tuesday. "I call upon you all, including the people's representatives, government officials and people from all walks of life to plant at least three saplings of fruits, timber and other medicinal trees and try to involve others with the government's three plantation movement." The prime minister later handed Bangabandhu National Award for Wild Life Conservation and Prime Minister National Award among the recipients for their outstanding contribution to preserving wild life and protecting environment through plantation. A Dhaka university teacher and two local government bodies received the Bangabandhu award, introduced for the first time. Forty-eight organisations and individuals were given prime minister award in 16 different categories for their contribution to tree plantation, and another six organisations and individuals for their work in social forestation. The Bangabandhu award recipients are professor emeritus Kazi Jaker Hossain, a teacher of Dhaka University's zoology department, Shilmaria Union Parishad of Puthia Upazila in Rajshahi and North Mikshimil Union Parishad of Dumuria Upazila in Khulna. Hasina handed over a cheque for Tk 1 lakh to the family of Rafiqul Alam from Teknaf in Cox's Bazar who was killed by forest 'pirates' whilw trying to protect the forest
